modules.description: Provides operations to create and manipulate intervals with associated values, including constructing from a lower and upper bound and a value, converting to and from a triplet format. Works with a polymorphic type that pairs a float interval with an arbitrary associated value. Used to represent ranges with metadata, such as time intervals with event data or numerical ranges with labels.

Provides tree traversal and node manipulation functions for interval trees, including insertion, deletion, and range queries. Operates on a custom tree structure where each node contains an interval and associated data. Used to efficiently manage and query overlapping time intervals in scheduling and spatial indexing applications.

creates and manages intervals with associated values, using a polymorphic type that pairs a float range with arbitrary data. It supports constructing intervals from bounds and values, converting to and from triplet representations, and handling range-based operations. This enables efficient storage and querying of data tied to numerical ranges, such as time-based events or labeled intervals. Examples include tracking scheduled tasks within time slots or associating metadata with numeric segments.
